The ORIGINAL ESPHome integration code in this repository — the Python
configuration/codegen and the C++ glue that wires Espressif's video stack into
ESPHome (for example esp_video_component.*, esp_cam_sensor_camera.*,
lvgl_camera_display.*, the *_custom_formats.h sensor tables, the build helpers
and the __init__.py files) — is licensed under the MIT License (reproduced
below).

This repository ALSO bundles ("vendors") substantial third-party source code
that is NOT licensed under MIT and is NOT relicensed by this file. Each such
component remains governed by the license of its original copyright owner. In
particular, the vendored Espressif Systems sources — the esp_video pipeline and
the esp_cam_sensor / esp_ipa / esp_sccb_intf drivers, together with their src/,
include/, private_include/, sensor/ trees and their idf_component / CMake /
linker files — are licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0, and carry
their own SPDX headers. See the NOTICE file for the full list and
LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt for the Apache-2.0 text.

These components are also ESPHome external components: they build on ESPHome,
which is itself dual-licensed (Python under MIT, C++/runtime under GPLv3). A
firmware compiled from this repository is a combined work and is, as a whole,
subject to ESPHome's terms as well.

When you build, distribute, or otherwise use this software you must comply with
BOTH the MIT License below AND the licenses of the bundled / upstream components
described in the NOTICE file.

